WEBVTT

01:10.651 --> 01:14.589
<i>In the beginning,
he already existed.</i>

01:15.324 --> 01:17.059
<i>He was with God.</i>

01:17.959 --> 01:21.096
<i>And he is God.</i>

01:21.130 --> 01:23.831
<i>Everything was created
through him.</i>

01:23.865 --> 01:27.702
<i>He gave life to everything
that was created,</i>

01:27.735 --> 01:32.141
<i>and his life brought
light to everyone.</i>

01:34.009 --> 01:37.645
<i>That light shines
in the darkness,</i>

01:37.678 --> 01:41.916
<i>and the darkness
can never extinguish it.</i>

01:43.018 --> 01:45.620
Haul them up
and head to shore!

01:45.653 --> 01:47.688
Hauling them up
and heading to shore!

01:47.722 --> 01:50.691
It's just another day at sea!

01:51.393 --> 01:54.962
For the boys
of Galilee!

02:02.737 --> 02:05.640
<i>♪ Before
we see the rising sun</i>

02:05.673 --> 02:09.277
<i>♪ Huh! Most of our work
is done</i>

02:09.311 --> 02:13.748
<i>♪ Huh-hah!
That is life here on the rolling sea</i>

02:13.781 --> 02:17.286
<i>♪ For the boys of Galilee</i>

02:19.388 --> 02:22.790
<i>♪ We know how to work
And we know how to fight</i>

02:22.824 --> 02:24.892
<i>♪ And if cheating
means winning</i>

02:24.926 --> 02:26.794
<i>♪ Who cares what's right?</i>

02:26.828 --> 02:28.863
<i>♪ A brother and a friend</i>

02:28.896 --> 02:30.365
<i>♪ We know who to trust
And who you can mock</i>

02:30.399 --> 02:32.401
<i>♪ Are trusted till the end</i>

02:32.434 --> 02:34.303
<i>♪ A net full of fish!
King of the Dock!</i>

02:34.336 --> 02:37.939
<i>♪ And it's just
another day at sea</i>

02:37.972 --> 02:43.178
<i>♪ For the boys</i>

02:43.212 --> 02:45.414
<i>♪ Of Galilee! ♪</i>

02:45.447 --> 02:48.383
Hoo! Hah!

02:48.417 --> 02:51.253
I won! Again.

02:51.286 --> 02:53.255
Boys of Galilee!

02:53.288 --> 02:56.058
Behold
my glorious catch.

02:56.091 --> 02:57.226
You.

02:59.261 --> 03:02.131
Peter!
Just in time.

03:02.164 --> 03:04.166
Uh, since you're
empty-handed,

03:04.199 --> 03:06.201
maybe you and your
little brother can help me

03:06.235 --> 03:08.237
with my huge net of fish.

03:08.270 --> 03:10.305
You tangled our nets.

03:10.339 --> 03:13.008
And you stole
our fishing spot!

03:13.041 --> 03:14.977
Who on earth
would do such a thing?

03:15.010 --> 03:16.744
Your spot?

03:16.777 --> 03:19.680
I had no idea you owned
the entire Galilee, Peter!

03:19.714 --> 03:22.151
Hey, at least I own
my own boat.

03:23.252 --> 03:25.053
That is our boat.

03:25.087 --> 03:26.954
Sure,
sons of Zebedee.

03:26.989 --> 03:28.290
And what's that
supposed to mean?

03:28.323 --> 03:30.292
Everybody knows your
father owns that boat

03:30.325 --> 03:31.893
just like everything else
in Capernaum.

03:31.926 --> 03:34.829
Yeah. Everything except
for these fish.

03:34.862 --> 03:37.865
These belong to me.

03:37.899 --> 03:40.768
You never know
when to quit, do you?

03:40.801 --> 03:42.471
- Never.
- Take them up.

03:43.771 --> 03:46.141
All righty, then,
away we go.

04:07.462 --> 04:09.131
Sorry.

04:09.164 --> 04:10.999
Out of my way!

04:13.968 --> 04:15.037
Don't move!

04:23.178 --> 04:24.313
Time to put an end
to this.

04:28.050 --> 04:28.984
And stay out!

04:29.985 --> 04:31.286
I'm sorry.

04:32.087 --> 04:33.888
Get back here!

04:33.921 --> 04:36.525
Hey, Petey, I got
a little something for you.

04:43.398 --> 04:45.866
My name's
not Petey.

04:45.900 --> 04:48.537
- Peter.
- Andrew. Quick.

04:48.570 --> 04:50.205
- Our fish! Let's go right now.
- No, no, no, no.

04:50.239 --> 04:51.106
James. Here they come.

04:52.474 --> 04:53.741
Get out of my way!

04:54.576 --> 04:55.776
Let's go!

05:02.217 --> 05:03.385
Sorry.

05:03.418 --> 05:04.752
Peter!

05:07.489 --> 05:08.991
Go, go, go.

05:12.261 --> 05:15.230
You want the fish? Fine.
Take them, then.

05:15.264 --> 05:17.165
More fish!

05:19.900 --> 05:22.170
Sons of thunder!

05:22.204 --> 05:24.539
Sons of thunder!

05:24.573 --> 05:27.109
Again.

05:27.142 --> 05:29.511
- Oh, there's my beautiful, bald brother.
- Whoo!

05:29.544 --> 05:32.014
Is that my reflection I see?

05:32.047 --> 05:34.149
Sons of thunder!

05:34.182 --> 05:36.351
- Yeah!
- Yeah! Ow!

05:36.385 --> 05:37.419
Ma, what're you doing?

05:37.452 --> 05:39.288
This is not how
I raised my sons.

05:39.321 --> 05:40.389
Mother, I was trying to stop...

05:43.225 --> 05:45.994
- Oh, so, you think this is funny, huh?
- Yeah. I do.

05:46.028 --> 05:47.828
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

05:50.065 --> 05:51.199
Where are your fish,
Abba?

05:51.233 --> 05:53.235
Malachi, not now.

05:53.268 --> 05:55.370
But why are your nets
so empty?

05:55.404 --> 05:57.439
Because they're thieves.

05:57.472 --> 05:59.174
The thieves
of Galilee,

05:59.207 --> 06:00.976
they stole my fish.

06:09.117 --> 06:10.085
What is wrong with you?

06:13.021 --> 06:13.821
Nothing.

06:16.024 --> 06:16.824
Nothing?

06:17.292 --> 06:18.527
Nothing.

06:18.560 --> 06:21.029
You call fist-fights
nothing?

06:21.063 --> 06:23.398
You call lashing out
on everyone around you,

06:23.432 --> 06:24.633
including your wife,
nothing?

06:24.666 --> 06:26.568
- I'm not lashing out.
- You are right now!

06:30.238 --> 06:31.340
We're drowning, Peter.

06:35.943 --> 06:37.612
We're fine.

06:37.646 --> 06:39.381
I'll get these nets
back in order,

06:39.414 --> 06:42.084
and in the morning,
I'll bring you back a net full of fish.

06:42.117 --> 06:43.851
- You watch.
- It's not about the fish.

06:45.354 --> 06:47.155
Not about the fish, Rachel?

06:47.756 --> 06:50.359
We sing songs about it.

06:50.392 --> 06:52.594
"A net full of fish
makes you king of the dock."

06:57.632 --> 07:00.402
More fish means
more money. Hmm?

07:00.435 --> 07:02.504
- And more money means that...
- What?

07:06.208 --> 07:07.042
It means what?

07:09.578 --> 07:11.613
Food on our table?

07:11.646 --> 07:14.349
Clothes on our back,
or another boat?

07:14.383 --> 07:16.051
Those things matter,
but, Peter...

07:16.084 --> 07:17.586
It means
I'm worth something.

07:24.192 --> 07:27.596
What matters
the most to me

07:27.629 --> 07:29.930
is how full
these nets are.

07:38.140 --> 07:39.541
I need to get back
to work.

07:45.680 --> 07:47.282
We'll help you untie
those knots.

07:47.315 --> 07:48.583
No, I can do it
on my own.

07:48.617 --> 07:50.918
- But I want to help, Papa.
- I don't need anyone's help!

07:53.655 --> 07:54.689
Rachel.

07:56.124 --> 07:57.526
Malachi.

07:57.559 --> 08:00.228
Let us know
when we matter.

08:07.335 --> 08:10.238
What, are you gonna squawk at
me, too?

08:10.272 --> 08:12.207
Huh?

08:18.280 --> 08:19.381
Of course.

08:48.743 --> 08:50.679
You're going
to give him your coat?

08:50.712 --> 08:51.746
Uh...

08:53.381 --> 08:54.349
Have you seen his hat?

08:55.283 --> 08:56.384
I gave him
more than that.

08:56.418 --> 08:59.020
Do I know you? Huh?

09:00.322 --> 09:03.992
And why are you standing
in my boat?

09:05.560 --> 09:06.728
Your net is empty, Peter.

09:06.761 --> 09:10.532
Oh, that is very
observant of you.

09:10.565 --> 09:12.267
You must be a prophet.

09:12.300 --> 09:14.736
It's empty
even when it's full of fish.

09:16.571 --> 09:17.806
That means you're ready.

09:17.839 --> 09:20.575
Hey. What are you...

09:20.609 --> 09:22.644
What do you mean,
I'm ready? Ready for what?

09:23.345 --> 09:25.680
Let's go out
into the deep.

09:25.714 --> 09:26.781
The deep.

09:26.815 --> 09:28.650
Look, Teacher.

09:28.683 --> 09:32.220
I don't know who you are
or how you think you know me,

09:32.254 --> 09:34.289
but if you don't mind,

09:34.322 --> 09:38.126
I need to figure this out
on my own.

09:38.159 --> 09:39.561
The boat is sailing,
son of John.

09:40.095 --> 09:41.663
You're gonna miss it.

09:41.696 --> 09:42.697
Peter, what's
he doing in our boat?

09:42.731 --> 09:44.199
Hey!

09:44.232 --> 09:45.634
Hey, look.
Peter's back at it again!

09:45.667 --> 09:48.637
Oh, I gotta see this.

09:48.670 --> 09:50.639
Hey, Pete.
While we're out there,

09:50.672 --> 09:52.507
maybe you can catch
my missing sandal.

09:53.775 --> 09:56.478
Peter!
Where are you going?

09:56.511 --> 09:58.513
- I don't know.
- And who is that with him?

10:01.116 --> 10:02.117
Are you ready, Peter?

10:02.651 --> 10:03.752
Sure.

10:07.656 --> 10:08.657
Row.

10:10.592 --> 10:12.127
Row.

10:26.374 --> 10:27.175
We're here.

10:28.643 --> 10:30.679
Here?

10:30.712 --> 10:34.683
I just spent three hours
in this exact place.

10:34.716 --> 10:36.351
It's an empty sea.

10:37.752 --> 10:39.254
That's not exactly true.

10:40.355 --> 10:41.389
Throw your net, Peter.

10:42.757 --> 10:44.626
Um, on the right side
of the boat.

10:44.659 --> 10:47.896
Oh, on the right side?

10:47.929 --> 10:50.198
You don't do a lot
of fishing, do you?

10:50.699 --> 10:52.167
No.

10:52.200 --> 10:54.636
So, uh,
what do you do?

10:54.669 --> 10:57.706
- Carpentry.
- Really?

10:57.739 --> 10:59.341
I can't believe
I'm doing this.

11:00.141 --> 11:01.676
You never did know
when to quit.

11:22.664 --> 11:24.000
Look.

11:24.033 --> 11:27.535
If you're trying to completely
humiliate me, then it's working.

11:30.839 --> 11:32.874
Hold on, ol' Peter!

11:40.749 --> 11:42.550
It's just another day
at sea

11:42.584 --> 11:44.586
for the boys of Galilee!

11:44.619 --> 11:46.521
I've never seen
anything like this!

11:46.554 --> 11:48.256
Andrew, are you gonna start
dancing or help me out here?

12:10.612 --> 12:12.781
Yeah! Yeah!

12:12.814 --> 12:14.282
Carpenter.

12:15.817 --> 12:17.552
I don't know who you are,

12:17.585 --> 12:19.954
but you must leave me
at once.

12:22.390 --> 12:24.426
I'm just a fisherman
from Galilee...

12:25.293 --> 12:28.963
a sinner, unworthy to be
in your presence.

12:28.998 --> 12:29.931
Peter.

12:32.600 --> 12:33.468
Follow me.

12:34.569 --> 12:36.204
And I will make you
a fisher of men.

12:37.472 --> 12:40.241
Andrew, follow me.

12:40.642 --> 12:41.977
James, John.

12:42.011 --> 12:44.345
Sons of thunder,
follow me!

12:44.379 --> 12:46.681
- Yes, I will.
- Me, too!

12:46.715 --> 12:48.950
Peter.
Our net is so full.

12:49.284 --> 12:51.486
Yes, it is.

12:51.519 --> 12:53.254
- He's the king of the dock!
- Andrew.

12:54.056 --> 12:56.324
I think
he's more than that.

12:56.357 --> 12:57.559
Yeah!

13:08.937 --> 13:10.605
How are you
doing that?

13:10.638 --> 13:12.707
I don't know.
The food just keeps coming.

13:12.741 --> 13:14.409
And so do the people.

13:14.442 --> 13:15.810
Look...

13:15.844 --> 13:17.278
That's the boy!

13:17.312 --> 13:18.847
The boy
with the miracle basket.

14:04.526 --> 14:06.262
Jesus did this, Papa.

14:08.663 --> 14:10.532
We don't need anymore.

14:11.900 --> 14:13.835
Everyone has
more than enough.

14:18.773 --> 14:20.042
Please.

14:20.075 --> 14:22.744
Please don't disturb
the teacher.

14:25.047 --> 14:27.116
Whoa, whoa!
Hey. I knew this would happen.

14:27.149 --> 14:28.650
Parents, please!

14:28.683 --> 14:31.053
Let the children come.

14:31.086 --> 14:33.721
Don't ignore any
of these little ones.

14:33.755 --> 14:36.391
Unless you become
like these little children,

14:36.424 --> 14:38.827
humble and full of faith,

14:38.860 --> 14:42.664
faith even as small as the
seed of a mustard flower,

14:42.697 --> 14:45.700
you can never come into the
Kingdom of Heaven.

14:45.733 --> 14:48.570
The spirit of the Lord
is upon me.

14:48.603 --> 14:50.939
The Father has sent me
to bring good news to you.

14:50.972 --> 14:52.841
To heal the brokenhearted.

14:52.874 --> 14:55.810
To tell you all that the
captives will be set free,

14:55.844 --> 14:57.512
the blind will see,

14:57.545 --> 14:59.514
the lame walk

14:59.547 --> 15:01.583
and the hurting
will be rescued.

15:02.750 --> 15:05.486
Oh! Thank you.

15:05.520 --> 15:07.622
Children,
look at these flowers.

15:07.655 --> 15:09.091
They don't make
their clothing,

15:09.124 --> 15:10.925
yet even
the great King Solomon

15:10.959 --> 15:13.561
was not dressed
as beautifully as they are.

15:14.662 --> 15:16.931
So, if God cares
so much for flowers

15:16.965 --> 15:19.901
that are here today
and gone tomorrow,

15:19.934 --> 15:22.071
don't you think
he cares for you, too?

15:22.104 --> 15:23.138
Yes!

15:23.172 --> 15:24.873
Oh, and look!

15:24.906 --> 15:26.507
Look at these birds!

15:26.541 --> 15:29.111
Look at how the Father
has provided for them.

15:32.982 --> 15:34.149
Why should you worry

15:34.183 --> 15:36.417
about what to eat and drink?

15:36.451 --> 15:39.188
Your Father
already knows your needs.

15:39.221 --> 15:42.523
Seek the heart of God
above everything else,

15:42.557 --> 15:45.060
and he will gladly give you
what you need.

15:45.094 --> 15:46.895
What is the heart of God?

15:48.230 --> 15:50.565
What is the heart of God?

15:50.598 --> 15:52.134
Have you ever heard
the story of the lost son?

15:53.534 --> 15:54.969
- No.
- No?

15:55.004 --> 15:56.938
Would you children
like to hear a story?

15:56.971 --> 15:58.406
- Yes!
- All right.

16:02.744 --> 16:03.811
Well...

16:04.946 --> 16:07.448
there was a kind
and wealthy farmer

16:07.482 --> 16:10.585
who had two sons
that he loved very much.

16:10.618 --> 16:13.122
He poured his life
into them.

16:13.155 --> 16:15.623
Well, these two boys were very
different from each other.

16:15.657 --> 16:18.693
The older son never cared
about life beyond the farm.

16:18.726 --> 16:21.562
He was satisfied
working his father's land

16:21.596 --> 16:24.532
and he looked forward to the day
when his own sons might take it over.

16:25.234 --> 16:27.236
But not so
with the youngest.

16:27.269 --> 16:30.239
He wanted nothing more
than to go into the world

16:30.272 --> 16:32.640
and indulge in everything
it had to offer.

16:34.742 --> 16:37.745
Why won't you
just let me go?

16:37.779 --> 16:40.648
There will be a day when you can
make that decision for yourself.

16:40.682 --> 16:43.551
But I love you, my son,
and I want what's best for you.

16:44.852 --> 16:45.820
Do you trust me?

16:46.155 --> 16:47.222
What?

16:47.256 --> 16:49.058
Dark thoughts crept
into his heart.

16:50.792 --> 16:52.827
He started to question
if he could trust his father.

16:53.962 --> 16:55.697
If he truly loves me,

16:56.764 --> 16:58.499
then he'll give me
what I want.

17:00.269 --> 17:02.204
So, the younger son
made up his mind

17:02.237 --> 17:05.707
and asked his father for his
share of the family wealth.

17:05.740 --> 17:07.608
Though his heart
was breaking,

17:07.642 --> 17:09.111
the father relented.

17:09.144 --> 17:11.046
He gave his son the money

17:11.079 --> 17:14.882
and watched this willful boy
set out on his own.

17:15.750 --> 17:17.118
Come home soon.

17:18.087 --> 17:19.954
This is goodbye, Father.

17:22.890 --> 17:24.993
He actually left.

17:25.027 --> 17:26.060
I can't believe it.

17:26.996 --> 17:28.763
I knew this day would come.

17:28.796 --> 17:29.931
Do you think
he'll ever come back?

17:31.333 --> 17:32.800
I'll always be waiting.

17:34.203 --> 17:35.937
Time passed.

17:35.970 --> 17:37.239
Weeks turned into months,

17:37.272 --> 17:39.540
and months turned
into seasons.

17:40.742 --> 17:42.844
Life on the farm
continued as normal.

17:42.877 --> 17:45.747
However, the father had not
heard from his youngest son

17:45.780 --> 17:47.082
since the day he left.

17:48.217 --> 17:51.753
The father longed
to hold him in his arms

17:51.786 --> 17:54.089
and protect him like he did
when he was just a boy.

17:55.224 --> 17:57.592
But his son had
to choose.

17:57.625 --> 17:59.294
And all the father could do
was watch...

18:00.229 --> 18:01.629
and wait.

18:03.265 --> 18:06.801
Sadly, the thing the father
feared most came true.

18:06.834 --> 18:09.570
His son spent
all of his inheritance

18:09.604 --> 18:12.640
on reckless living
and could barely get by.

18:12.673 --> 18:15.310
And about this time,
a severe famine hit the land.

18:18.013 --> 18:20.182
Now, penniless

18:20.882 --> 18:22.884
and homeless,

18:22.917 --> 18:25.653
he went and hired himself out
to a local pig farmer.

18:28.790 --> 18:31.026
As he sat out
among the swine,

18:31.060 --> 18:33.828
his empty stomach groaned.

18:33.861 --> 18:36.597
He scrounged through
the mud for scraps of food,

18:36.631 --> 18:38.300
fighting the pigs
for anything edible.

18:39.967 --> 18:42.004
It was at this moment

18:42.037 --> 18:44.605
he realized
how far he had fallen.

18:45.740 --> 18:48.143
What has become of me?

18:48.177 --> 18:51.612
Even my father's
servants have shelter

18:51.646 --> 18:53.148
and more than enough food.

18:54.849 --> 18:56.285
Look at me.

18:56.318 --> 18:57.919
Look at me.

18:59.321 --> 19:00.655
Look at me!

19:02.191 --> 19:03.691
I miss my father.

19:05.294 --> 19:06.894
I miss you, Father.

19:08.663 --> 19:11.833
So the young man
arose from his filth,

19:12.600 --> 19:15.736
and he began
his long journey home.

19:18.407 --> 19:19.341
Weak,

19:20.075 --> 19:22.877
barefoot and broken,

19:22.910 --> 19:26.081
he came within sight
of the old homestead.

19:26.115 --> 19:28.383
And while he was still
a long way off,

19:28.417 --> 19:30.152
his father saw him.

19:31.819 --> 19:32.820
My son?

19:34.123 --> 19:36.024
- My son!
- Father.

19:36.058 --> 19:37.625
- My son!
- Father!

19:39.760 --> 19:41.130
I have sinned

19:41.163 --> 19:44.032
against God
and against you.

19:44.066 --> 19:47.735
I am no longer worthy to be
called your son.

19:49.104 --> 19:51.039
But you are my son.

19:52.074 --> 19:54.042
Nothing will
ever change that.

19:54.076 --> 19:55.843
I love you.

19:55.877 --> 19:57.845
And I love you.

19:57.879 --> 20:00.315
Now, I will give you
my best coat

20:00.349 --> 20:03.318
and put it on you,
and take my ring and put it on your hand,

20:03.352 --> 20:04.919
and put shoes on your feet.

20:04.952 --> 20:06.989
We will have a feast
and celebrate!

20:09.458 --> 20:11.759
For you were dead,
but now you are alive.

20:12.927 --> 20:14.962
You were lost,
but now you are found.

20:15.998 --> 20:18.100
You are safely home,
my son.

20:19.401 --> 20:20.801
Oman!

20:20.835 --> 20:22.271
- Oman!
- Yes, master?

20:22.304 --> 20:23.905
Kill the fattened calf.

20:25.806 --> 20:28.809
My son is home.

20:29.044 --> 20:30.179
Yes!

20:30.912 --> 20:32.080
Yes!

20:32.947 --> 20:34.316
Praise God.

20:35.850 --> 20:37.486
My friends.

20:37.519 --> 20:39.954
That is the heart
of your heavenly Father.

20:41.190 --> 20:43.891
Teacher,
how should we pray to Him?

20:43.925 --> 20:45.394
- Please teach us.
- Yes, master.

20:46.495 --> 20:47.795
When you pray to your Abba,

20:48.297 --> 20:49.364
your Father...

20:50.831 --> 20:51.433
pray like this.

20:54.036 --> 20:55.803
Our Father in heaven,

20:57.039 --> 20:58.739
may your name be kept holy.

20:59.274 --> 21:00.808
May your kingdom come

21:00.841 --> 21:03.178
and your will be done
on Earth,

21:03.212 --> 21:04.279
as it is in heaven.

21:05.480 --> 21:07.482
Give us what we need today

21:07.516 --> 21:10.419
and forgive us of our sins,
as we have forgiven those

21:10.452 --> 21:11.453
who have sinned against us.

21:12.820 --> 21:14.389
And don't let us give
into temptation.

21:14.423 --> 21:16.291
But rescue us
from the evil one.

21:17.426 --> 21:19.328
For yours is the kingdom

21:19.961 --> 21:21.929
and the power and the glory...

21:23.065 --> 21:24.066
forever.

21:25.133 --> 21:26.301
Amen.

21:26.335 --> 21:28.003
- Amen.
- Amen.

21:28.036 --> 21:29.770
- Amen!
- You agree, then?

21:29.804 --> 21:31.106
Yes.

21:31.139 --> 21:33.275
I must go and bring
this good news to others.

21:33.308 --> 21:34.476
Blessings to all of you.

21:34.509 --> 21:37.546
And remember, if you have ears to
hear, let them hear.

21:37.579 --> 21:40.182
If you have eyes to see,
let them see.

21:46.188 --> 21:48.323
Jesus. Jesus.

21:48.357 --> 21:50.392
If we want to get to Jerusalem
in time for the Passover,

21:50.425 --> 21:51.792
we need to be
on our way.

21:51.826 --> 21:54.563
Yes. Judas always
thinking ahead.

21:54.596 --> 21:56.265
But first I'd like
to stop at Martha's house

21:56.298 --> 21:57.499
before we get
into Jerusalem.

21:57.532 --> 21:59.468
Ha! I was hoping
he would say that.

21:59.501 --> 22:02.070
Why? Because Martha
is a better cook than Rachel?

22:02.104 --> 22:04.239
- I never said that.
- No!

22:04.273 --> 22:05.173
But you meant it.

22:07.576 --> 22:09.511
Hi, my love.

22:09.544 --> 22:11.313
Oh, how sweet!

22:11.346 --> 22:13.315
Look at them, Rachel.
They're like new men.

22:13.348 --> 22:14.383
I haven't even
seen them fight

22:14.416 --> 22:16.351
since they started
following Jesus.

22:16.385 --> 22:18.520
Because they stopped
fighting themselves.

22:20.055 --> 22:21.123
Leper!

22:21.156 --> 22:22.491
Leper, go.

22:22.524 --> 22:23.358
Unclean.

22:25.027 --> 22:26.961
- Unclean.
- It's a leper.

22:26.995 --> 22:28.230
Everyone, clear away!

22:28.263 --> 22:29.864
- Get back!
- Get Jesus away from him.

22:29.897 --> 22:31.266
- Master, let's go this way.
- No!

22:31.300 --> 22:32.434
Master, don't.

22:32.467 --> 22:33.602
I can't let you
touch him.

22:33.635 --> 22:35.037
His disease
is a death sentence.

22:36.204 --> 22:37.205
What is your name?

22:38.106 --> 22:39.441
Unclean.

22:41.043 --> 22:44.246
But if you are willing,

22:44.279 --> 22:46.148
you can make me
clean again.

22:46.181 --> 22:47.149
What? No.

22:47.182 --> 22:48.849
Master, stay back.

22:48.883 --> 22:50.252
- Jesus, do not touch him.
- John.

22:50.285 --> 22:52.054
- John!
- No!

22:52.087 --> 22:53.588
Don't touch him!

22:58.627 --> 23:00.961
Your faith
has made you clean.

23:14.543 --> 23:15.544
Ah.

23:16.111 --> 23:16.911
Ah!

23:17.279 --> 23:18.280
My face?

23:19.581 --> 23:21.049
Am I healed?

23:31.159 --> 23:32.494
Praise be to God.

23:35.163 --> 23:36.331
Praise be to God.

23:38.333 --> 23:39.967
Praise be to God.

23:43.505 --> 23:45.873
Praise be to God!

23:48.043 --> 23:51.213
Praise be to God!

23:51.246 --> 23:52.880
- Master, you just...
- I did.

23:54.282 --> 23:56.151
- Yeah, but he was a...
- He was.

24:01.022 --> 24:02.224
John.

24:04.559 --> 24:05.926
Sing the Passover song.

24:08.997 --> 24:10.399
Okay.

24:12.200 --> 24:13.235
Let's go
to Jerusalem.

