<i>♪ City of gold</i>

25:21.369 --> 25:23.438
<i>♪ Jerusalem</i>

25:23.472 --> 25:25.307
<i>♪ City of light</i>

25:25.340 --> 25:27.342
<i>♪ Jerusalem</i>

25:27.375 --> 25:29.411
<i>♪ Jerusalem</i>

25:29.444 --> 25:32.013
<i>♪ City of promise</i>

25:32.047 --> 25:34.115
<i>♪ Bright in the night</i>

25:34.149 --> 25:35.617
<i>♪ Jerusalem ♪</i>

25:43.425 --> 25:46.328
Young lady, Jerusalem
is in that direction.

25:46.361 --> 25:49.130
I'm not going to Jerusalem.
I'm looking for someone.

25:49.164 --> 25:51.333
The only one you should be
seeking right now is God.

25:51.366 --> 25:54.636
And he's not behind us.
He's ahead in Jerusalem.

25:56.538 --> 25:58.039
Mary?

25:58.073 --> 26:00.308
Mary? Where were you?

26:00.342 --> 26:02.511
Jesus and the boys
will be here any minute.

26:02.544 --> 26:03.812
And I'm still making mutton.

26:03.845 --> 26:05.547
- They're here.
- Already?

26:07.849 --> 26:08.783
Amah!

26:12.287 --> 26:13.321
Rachel.

26:14.689 --> 26:15.757
Mother Mary.

26:17.425 --> 26:19.294
Well, we came on ahead.

26:19.327 --> 26:20.829
The boys will be here soon.

26:20.862 --> 26:23.632
Mary, can you help me
with this food?

26:23.665 --> 26:25.400
You stay here.
I'll help Martha.

26:26.301 --> 26:29.070
Oh, I'm so excited
to hear the latest news.

26:29.104 --> 26:31.106
- What's been happening?
- Where do we begin?

26:31.139 --> 26:34.409
He just fed 5,000 men,
plus the women and children

26:34.442 --> 26:36.211
with five loaves
of bread and two fish,

26:36.244 --> 26:38.346
healed a leper,
raised a child from the dead

26:38.380 --> 26:41.249
and delivered this Magdalean
woman here from seven demons.

26:41.550 --> 26:42.684
Say, hi.

26:44.519 --> 26:45.787
Hi.

26:46.588 --> 26:48.823
My name is Mary.
What's your name?

26:50.492 --> 26:52.594
- Mary.
- Mary!

26:52.627 --> 26:54.462
Help Mother Mary
with the food.

26:55.297 --> 26:56.364
Who is she?

26:58.233 --> 26:59.734
Mary.

26:59.768 --> 27:02.070
Another one?

27:03.538 --> 27:06.074
Well, let's all eat, drink
and, uh, be merry.

27:06.875 --> 27:08.810
Mama. Where's Lazarus?

27:08.843 --> 27:10.812
I'm sure he's
around here somewhere,

27:10.845 --> 27:13.848
but before you run off,
you need to wash your hands.

27:15.383 --> 27:17.686
- Lazarus.
- Malachi!

27:17.719 --> 27:20.822
That boy
doesn't sit still for a minute.

27:20.855 --> 27:22.824
He's just
like his father.

27:22.857 --> 27:24.893
That's just the way
John was,

27:24.926 --> 27:27.429
always off on some adventure.

27:27.462 --> 27:28.863
But, oh, what a sweet boy,

27:29.764 --> 27:31.700
just the opposite
of James.

27:31.733 --> 27:32.767
How so?

27:32.801 --> 27:34.669
Mr. know-it-all,
that one.

27:34.703 --> 27:37.238
Always had an answer
for everything.

27:37.272 --> 27:39.341
I wore my belt out on his behind.

27:41.176 --> 27:43.478
I bet Jesus never
gave you any trouble, Mary.

27:44.679 --> 27:46.715
What was that?

27:46.748 --> 27:48.450
That means
there was something!

27:48.483 --> 27:50.352
There had
to be something. Tell us.

27:50.385 --> 27:51.720
Come on. You have
to tell us everything.

27:52.287 --> 27:54.389
Well,

27:54.422 --> 27:57.525
when Jesus was
about Malachi's age,

27:57.559 --> 28:01.763
we were traveling back with the
caravan from Jerusalem after Passover.

28:01.796 --> 28:03.732
And I assumed
he was with Joseph,

28:03.765 --> 28:06.267
and Joseph assumed
he was with me.

28:06.301 --> 28:08.236
So, you can imagine
how shocked we were

28:08.269 --> 28:10.538
when we realized
he wasn't with either of us.

28:10.572 --> 28:12.907
I would've
ripped into him.

28:14.843 --> 28:16.511
Where was he?

28:16.544 --> 28:19.681
Oh, we finally found him three
days later back in Jerusalem.

28:20.715 --> 28:22.350
- Jerusalem?
- Jerusalem?

28:22.384 --> 28:24.886
And he never told you
or Joseph he was going back?

28:24.919 --> 28:26.821
Oh, I would've ripped
into him.

28:26.855 --> 28:30.492
He was at the
temple teaching the rabbis.

28:31.793 --> 28:34.729
God instructed Moses

28:34.763 --> 28:36.564
to put the blood
of their lambs

28:36.598 --> 28:39.200
over the doorways
of their homes

28:39.234 --> 28:40.902
so that death can pass
over them.

28:40.935 --> 28:44.305
Yes, for the covering
of our sins.

28:44.339 --> 28:46.908
But if the blood
of the Passover lamb

28:46.941 --> 28:49.411
forgives the sins
of the people,

28:49.444 --> 28:51.846
why must we sacrifice it
every year?

28:51.880 --> 28:54.249
The Passover lamb
must be sacrificed every year

28:54.282 --> 28:56.951
because there is no
permanent cure for man's sin.

28:56.986 --> 29:00.522
Therefore we must always
provide a lamb to be slain,

29:00.555 --> 29:02.223
just as the law requires.

29:02.257 --> 29:05.527
Have you forgotten
that God told Abraham,

29:05.560 --> 29:08.229
"I will provide the lamb,"

29:08.263 --> 29:12.367
and through him, all the nations
of the Earth will be blessed?

29:12.400 --> 29:14.436
This boy speaks
with authority and wisdom.

29:14.469 --> 29:16.471
Oh, you're speaking
of the messiah.

29:16.504 --> 29:17.739
Yes.

29:17.772 --> 29:19.974
Our messiah will come
as a warrior,

29:20.009 --> 29:21.776
conquering the nations

29:21.810 --> 29:24.212
and restoring glory
to Israel.

29:24.612 --> 29:26.281
No.

29:26.314 --> 29:28.950
He will come as God's lamb
to be sacrificed.

29:28.984 --> 29:31.286
His blood will break
the power of sin

29:31.319 --> 29:33.254
that separates man
from God,

29:34.322 --> 29:35.390
once and for all.

29:35.423 --> 29:36.825
Amazing!

29:36.858 --> 29:39.828
How does this boy
speak like this?

29:39.861 --> 29:41.997
It sounds
as if you know him.

29:43.598 --> 29:45.266
Tell me, boy.

29:45.300 --> 29:47.702
If you know so much
about the messiah,

29:48.470 --> 29:49.704
who is he?

29:50.672 --> 29:52.974
Jesus! Oh!

29:53.008 --> 29:55.443
They were amazed by him.

29:56.911 --> 29:59.948
But Joseph and I
were too upset to care.

29:59.982 --> 30:02.484
We scolded him right there
in front of the Pharisees.

30:03.852 --> 30:05.320
What did he do?

30:06.488 --> 30:09.491
He just looked up at me
and said...

30:09.524 --> 30:10.993
"Didn't you know
I'd be in my Father's house?"

30:20.702 --> 30:22.004
That's it?

30:23.905 --> 30:25.040
That's all he said?

30:26.474 --> 30:29.044
Well
I'll tell you one thing.

30:29.078 --> 30:31.880
If that were James or John,
I would've grabbed them by the ears

30:31.913 --> 30:33.314
and whooped
their little behinds.

30:35.450 --> 30:37.852
Especially
if it were James.

30:37.886 --> 30:40.922
Mmm-hmm. I would've
gathered the entire caravan

30:40.955 --> 30:42.590
and made him do
a public apology

30:42.624 --> 30:44.726
for turning my hair gray

30:44.759 --> 30:47.462
and making his father go bald.

30:47.495 --> 30:49.031
Yes, ma'am.
Listen.

30:49.064 --> 30:51.766
I would've even made him
apologize to the donkey.

30:51.800 --> 30:53.802
For having to walk
all the way back to Jerusalem.

30:53.835 --> 30:55.370
And then what?

30:55.403 --> 30:57.505
Then I would've
told that little boy Jesus...

30:57.539 --> 30:58.840
What, Amah?

31:03.045 --> 31:05.346
That God chose the right
woman to be your mother.

31:07.082 --> 31:08.516
- That he did.
- Help me down.

31:09.484 --> 31:10.485
Amah.

31:11.753 --> 31:12.787
Mother.

31:14.923 --> 31:16.491
Martha, my home away from home.

31:16.524 --> 31:18.493
Jesus. Oh!

31:18.526 --> 31:20.728
You are skin and bones.
Now, come.

31:20.762 --> 31:22.031
Sit. I just made fig cakes.

31:22.064 --> 31:23.565
Mary, go get
the fig cakes.

31:23.598 --> 31:24.532
We can't stay for long.

31:24.566 --> 31:26.868
Peter is keeping us
on a very tight schedule.

31:26.901 --> 31:29.071
Hey! Get out
of my kitchen.

31:29.104 --> 31:30.839
You are all like
a pack of jackals!

31:30.872 --> 31:32.674
Now, there is more
in the oven.

31:32.707 --> 31:33.942
Get out, James.

32:12.447 --> 32:13.748
Mary?

32:13.781 --> 32:16.384
Now, Mary, I just
asked you to go get the...

32:19.221 --> 32:20.622
Jesus.

32:20.655 --> 32:21.789
Don't you think it's unfair

32:21.823 --> 32:25.027
that my sister just sits there
while I do all the work?

32:25.060 --> 32:26.394
Tell her to come
and help me.

32:28.030 --> 32:29.497
Martha...

32:30.431 --> 32:32.867
there is only one thing
worth being concerned about...

32:33.935 --> 32:35.403
and Mary has found it.

32:38.473 --> 32:39.841
And it will not be
taken away from her.

32:43.478 --> 32:45.780
Besides,
I never really liked your cooking.

32:46.881 --> 32:49.751
- I love it!
- Jesus!

32:49.784 --> 32:52.687
- Jesus!
- There he is! Lazarus!

32:52.720 --> 32:55.190
- Hey. You've gotten taller.
- And stronger.

32:55.224 --> 32:57.092
What has Martha
been feeding you?

32:57.126 --> 32:59.228
What hasn't she
been feeding him.

32:59.261 --> 33:01.096
Lazarus, come with us
to Jerusalem,

33:01.130 --> 33:02.164
if it's all right
with your sisters.

33:02.197 --> 33:04.632
All right?
Oh, please, get him out of here.

33:04.666 --> 33:07.202
You know, every day his
friends from the city come,

33:07.236 --> 33:08.937
and guess who has
to feed them? Me.

33:08.970 --> 33:11.140
Hey, go raid their
cupboards for once,

33:11.173 --> 33:12.840
and then come back here
and rest!

33:12.874 --> 33:14.776
All right! We need
to be on our way.

33:14.809 --> 33:16.211
- Be safe!
- Goodbye, Mary.

33:17.212 --> 33:18.446
Goodbye!

33:28.623 --> 33:32.961
<i>♪ Jerusalem city of gold</i>

33:32.995 --> 33:35.530
<i>♪ Jerusalem city of light</i>

33:36.898 --> 33:41.270
<i>♪ Jerusalem, Jerusalem</i>

33:41.303 --> 33:44.539
<i>♪ City of promise
bright in the night ♪</i>

33:51.046 --> 33:52.780
Don't go
near that man, Sarah.

33:54.582 --> 33:58.486
He was born blind.
God's curse is on him.

33:58.920 --> 34:00.222
All right, Mama.

34:03.591 --> 34:04.492
Teacher...

34:06.095 --> 34:08.730
why was this man
born blind?

34:08.763 --> 34:11.498
Was it because of his own
sins or his parents' sins?

34:11.766 --> 34:13.768
Neither.

34:13.801 --> 34:17.638
This happened so that the power
of God could be seen in him.

34:17.672 --> 34:21.542
This man lives in darkness, but
today, Judas, he will see the light.

34:22.844 --> 34:26.748
Shekel? Have mercy.
Just one shekel, sir?

34:41.196 --> 34:42.764
It looks like
he's making mud.

34:50.804 --> 34:52.274
No.
What are you doing?

34:56.643 --> 35:00.182
Please, please
don't shame me more, please.

35:01.916 --> 35:03.352
Now go,

35:03.385 --> 35:05.586
and wash yourself
in the Pool of Siloam.

35:06.121 --> 35:07.322
The healing pool?

35:07.622 --> 35:08.823
Yes.

35:10.691 --> 35:12.560
You're smiling.

35:13.062 --> 35:15.097
- I am.
- Yes.

35:15.130 --> 35:16.331
Yes, I will go to the pool.

35:19.301 --> 35:20.568
Thank you.

35:23.838 --> 35:25.240
What is your name?

35:26.308 --> 35:27.309
Jesus.

35:28.010 --> 35:29.577
Jesus.

35:30.878 --> 35:31.779
Jesus.

35:33.382 --> 35:34.349
Jesus.

35:37.219 --> 35:38.320
Teacher,

35:39.021 --> 35:41.156
why did you put mud
on his eyes?

35:42.291 --> 35:44.359
Because, Nathanael,

35:44.393 --> 35:45.994
sometimes things have
to get messier

35:46.028 --> 35:47.595
before they can be
truly clean.

35:51.233 --> 35:54.236
<i>♪ Jerusalem</i>

35:57.039 --> 35:59.607
<i>♪ Jerusalem ♪</i>

36:15.690 --> 36:18.026
Purchase your
Passover sacrifices here! Oh.

36:18.060 --> 36:21.363
Need more forgiveness than
usual this year.

36:21.396 --> 36:23.865
Two doves
for one copper coin!

36:23.898 --> 36:25.833
No blemish! No blemish!

36:25.867 --> 36:29.071
Imported sacrificial knives
all the way from Egypt.

36:29.104 --> 36:31.806
Head coverings!
Buy now, get another one at half!

36:31.839 --> 36:34.343
This one was touched
and blessed by the Sanhedrin.

36:34.376 --> 36:37.678
This one was touched by Caiaphas himself!
It's anointed. You buy?

36:37.712 --> 36:41.682
Master. Do we buy our Passover
sacrifices here or should we wait?

36:41.716 --> 36:43.252
You need to buy it here!
Buy now!

36:45.287 --> 36:48.290
My Passover lambs'
feet have never touched the ground.

36:48.323 --> 36:50.758
A perfect sacrifice
sure to please Jehovah.

36:50.791 --> 36:53.462
Wrapped in swaddling cloth
from Bethlehem.

36:53.495 --> 36:55.430
Can you believe
that over one million people

36:55.464 --> 36:57.698
come here
for these three days?

36:57.732 --> 36:59.001
Oh, yes, I can.

36:59.034 --> 37:01.170
Of course they would
be selling phylacteries here.

37:01.203 --> 37:03.071
Now why didn't I think
of that?

37:03.105 --> 37:05.706
- They must be making a killing.
- They do.

37:08.743 --> 37:10.379
You despicable little brat!

37:10.412 --> 37:11.746
Let me go!
Let me go!

37:17.286 --> 37:18.153
Hey!

37:20.088 --> 37:22.224
You're going to pay
for that shofar!

37:22.257 --> 37:25.793
The Scriptures declare, "My temple
will be called a house of prayer."

37:25.826 --> 37:26.727
Wait a minute.

37:29.797 --> 37:33.968
My temple will be called
a house of prayer!

37:34.002 --> 37:37.072
But you have turned it
into a den of thieves!

37:54.489 --> 37:57.825
This is my Father's house!

38:03.265 --> 38:05.434
This is my Father's house!

38:08.836 --> 38:11.206
No!
It cannot touch the ground!

38:13.008 --> 38:13.808
Get out!

38:16.478 --> 38:19.780
My Father does not want
your goats for sacrificing!

38:20.948 --> 38:23.252
He does not want
the blood of your bulls!

38:24.019 --> 38:27.055
What he wants is you.
He wants you.

38:35.830 --> 38:37.832
Where is your love
for the Father?

38:37.865 --> 38:38.766
You are insolent.

38:44.039 --> 38:45.540
- Stay back!
- Jesus.

38:45.574 --> 38:47.409
Get back.

38:47.442 --> 38:50.479
All right, brothers!
It's time to fight!

38:50.512 --> 38:51.580
That's not
what Jesus wants!

38:51.613 --> 38:55.150
This is it. This is Jesus
bringing God's kingdom.

38:55.183 --> 38:56.551
Let us fight with him!

38:56.585 --> 38:58.253
What, and die with him? No way!

38:58.287 --> 39:02.124
No! He doesn't want us
to fight. Not like this.

39:02.157 --> 39:03.325
Ahhh!

39:04.226 --> 39:05.027
Who did this?

39:06.995 --> 39:08.497
Who did this?

39:12.867 --> 39:14.902
You!

39:14.935 --> 39:18.839
You dare to disgrace
the temple of the Lord?

39:20.609 --> 39:21.543
You!

39:21.576 --> 39:24.912
Now there's room for
the blind and the sick.

39:28.116 --> 39:31.386
What?
Get out of here!

39:31.420 --> 39:34.022
- Peter, Peter.
- Where are the temple guards?

39:34.056 --> 39:35.090
- Run.
- Go after him.

39:35.123 --> 39:36.291
Keep him there, Malchus.

39:36.325 --> 39:37.825
Hey, you can't...

39:40.395 --> 39:43.031
Caiaphas,
your holiness.

39:43.065 --> 39:45.500
Caiaphas,
I can assure you,

39:45.534 --> 39:47.902
we will deal with the man
who did this.

39:48.570 --> 39:50.971
One man did all this?

39:51.006 --> 39:53.508
We pursued the vandal, sir,

39:53.542 --> 39:56.645
but lost him and his gang
of Galileans in the crowd.

39:56.678 --> 39:58.913
Here are some of the men
who were with him.

40:01.383 --> 40:04.885
I did not participate in this
rebellion, I can assure you.

40:05.987 --> 40:08.323
A fish out of water.

40:08.357 --> 40:12.427
You Galileans have
a certain smell about you.

40:12.461 --> 40:16.565
- We're not all Galileans, sir.
- No?

40:16.598 --> 40:17.632
What's your name?

40:18.667 --> 40:20.168
Judas Iscariot.

40:22.104 --> 40:25.906
I am a successful merchant who
has done a lot of business.

40:28.276 --> 40:29.678
Right here, actually.

40:29.711 --> 40:33.382
Judas. Please tell
those lowly net-casters

40:33.415 --> 40:35.450
that there are no fish here

40:35.484 --> 40:38.186
for them to draw into
their rebellious delusion.

40:38.220 --> 40:40.589
An empty sea.

40:40.622 --> 40:43.392
What did you say?

40:43.425 --> 40:45.093
It's what
we lowly fishermen call

40:46.094 --> 40:47.529
an empty sea.

40:53.335 --> 40:54.669
What is your name?

40:56.304 --> 40:57.439
Peter.

40:57.472 --> 40:58.673
- Peter.
- Yeah.

41:03.111 --> 41:07.182
I will have your leader caged
for what he has done.

41:07.215 --> 41:11.319
Tell him we will be watching and
to never enter God's house again.

41:12.687 --> 41:14.356
And a word of advice,
fisherman.

41:14.389 --> 41:17.025
Go back to your boat
and abandon this cause.

41:17.058 --> 41:19.561
Religion has no place
for someone like you.

41:22.097 --> 41:25.066
If this is what your religion is...

41:25.100 --> 41:26.967
then I have no place
for it.

41:29.538 --> 41:31.706
Judas,

41:31.740 --> 41:34.276
a wise merchant knows
when to cut his losses.

41:40.115 --> 41:42.050
Isn't this the beggar
from the gate?

41:42.083 --> 41:44.386
Well,
it looks like him,

41:44.419 --> 41:46.721
but it can't be.
He's blind.

41:46.755 --> 41:49.191
He was found at the Pool
of Siloam causing trouble,

41:49.224 --> 41:52.394
claiming Jesus of Nazareth
healed him of his blindness.

41:52.427 --> 41:54.663
- Who is Jesus of Nazareth?
- That's the man who did this.

41:55.664 --> 41:58.133
Some say he is a rabbi,

41:58.166 --> 42:02.103
but I heard he's merely
the son of a carpenter.

42:02.137 --> 42:04.005
You are the blind beggar,
aren't you?

42:04.039 --> 42:05.474
Yes, I am.

42:06.641 --> 42:07.709
Or I was.

42:11.613 --> 42:14.249
Yes, yes, you're Nicodemus.

42:14.282 --> 42:16.751
You've put many coins
in my cup over the years.

42:16.785 --> 42:18.720
How do we know this man
is telling the truth?

42:19.621 --> 42:21.623
I am his mother.

42:21.656 --> 42:25.527
I can testify that this is
my son and he was born blind.

42:25.560 --> 42:28.563
Yes, but how can he
now see?

42:28.597 --> 42:31.099
He is old enough to speak for himself.
Ask him.

42:31.132 --> 42:32.000
Enough!

42:38.106 --> 42:40.442
We will give God
the glory for this healing,

42:41.576 --> 42:43.211
but let there be no confusion.

42:43.245 --> 42:48.049
This Jesus is a sinner
who causes others to sin.

42:48.083 --> 42:50.385
I don't know whether
he is a sinner or not.

42:50.418 --> 42:52.087
But I do know this,

42:52.120 --> 42:55.123
I was blind,
and now I can see!

42:56.358 --> 42:58.293
I recognize your walk.

42:58.326 --> 43:01.062
Every day for years,
I've heard you walk right by me,

43:01.096 --> 43:04.533
but Jesus stopped
and saw me.

43:04.566 --> 43:06.468
How did he heal you?

43:06.501 --> 43:08.169
Ask the one
who sent him.

43:09.538 --> 43:12.707
And who do you believe
sent him?

43:15.110 --> 43:16.745
God.

43:16.778 --> 43:18.580
Heretic! Heretic!
This man is a heretic!

43:18.613 --> 43:19.748
Blasphemy!

43:21.349 --> 43:23.385
Clear this place now!

43:23.418 --> 43:25.353
Nicodemus!

43:25.387 --> 43:27.789
Gather your staff and get this
mess cleaned up before morning.

43:29.224 --> 43:31.159
It's going to be business
as usual.

43:52.914 --> 43:56.518
"And when he comes,
he will open the eyes of the blind...

43:58.553 --> 44:00.889
"and unplug
the ears of the deaf."

44:00.922 --> 44:03.191
"The lame
will leap like a deer,

44:03.224 --> 44:05.293
"and those who cannot speak
will sing for joy."

44:05.327 --> 44:06.194
Isaiah's prophecy.

44:07.329 --> 44:09.364
Could it be?

44:09.397 --> 44:11.866
In our lifetime, Joseph?

44:11.900 --> 44:14.102
It has to happen
in somebody's lifetime, Nic.

44:15.403 --> 44:16.605
Why not ours?

44:23.578 --> 44:24.713
Who do you think he is?

44:27.282 --> 44:29.384
A carpenter,

44:29.417 --> 44:32.387
who continues to fulfill every
prophecy written about the Messiah.

44:40.862 --> 44:44.566
<i>♪ So many
years within these walls</i>

44:44.599 --> 44:48.370
<i>♪ I've studied our laws
night and day</i>

44:48.403 --> 44:51.906
<i>♪ My life was planned
My path was known</i>

44:51.940 --> 44:56.945
<i>♪ No doubt or fear stood
in my way</i>

44:56.979 --> 45:00.248
<i>♪ But I can't believe
what I have seen</i>

45:00.281 --> 45:02.884
<i>♪ How could this peasant
heal the blind?</i>

45:03.818 --> 45:06.788
<i>♪ Now I'm the one groping
in the dark</i>

45:06.821 --> 45:12.160
<i>♪ Do I seek
what I'm afraid to find?</i>

45:13.395 --> 45:16.798
<i>♪ Is this real what I've seen?</i>

45:16.831 --> 45:20.368
<i>♪ Is this man
the promised King?</i>

45:20.402 --> 45:26.641
<i>♪ Is my world closing in
around me?</i>

45:26.675 --> 45:29.844
<i>♪ Am I trapped in these walls?</i>

45:30.945 --> 45:34.549
<i>♪ Am I deaf to his call?</i>

45:34.582 --> 45:37.552
<i>♪ And am I the blind man?</i>

45:37.585 --> 45:39.521
<i>♪ Am I the blind man</i>

45:40.955 --> 45:45.393
<i>♪ After all? ♪</i>

45:53.568 --> 45:54.769
Jesus.

45:56.304 --> 45:57.305
Nicodemus.

45:59.008 --> 46:02.911
No one can do what you have
done unless God is with them.

46:02.944 --> 46:04.746
I do what my Father
tells me to do.

46:05.981 --> 46:07.449
Just like it's done in heaven.

46:08.450 --> 46:10.485
Your Father?

46:10.518 --> 46:13.955
But you're just the son of a
carpenter, from Nazareth,

46:14.956 --> 46:16.224
aren't you?

46:17.059 --> 46:18.827
Not entirely.

46:20.795 --> 46:22.864
What do you want,
Nicodemus?

46:25.400 --> 46:26.568
I want to see heaven.

46:27.736 --> 46:29.004
And you can.

46:29.838 --> 46:31.639
But first you must
be born again.

46:33.441 --> 46:36.711
How can a grown man
like me be born again?

46:37.946 --> 46:39.881
Do you feel that?

46:40.882 --> 46:43.618
You can hear the wind
rustling through the leaves,

46:43.651 --> 46:46.688
but you don't know where it
came from or where it's going.

46:46.721 --> 46:48.323
That is how the spirit
of God is.

46:50.925 --> 46:53.294
People can only reproduce
human life...

46:54.295 --> 46:57.332
but the spirit of God
gives birth to spiritual life.

46:58.900 --> 47:01.003
You were already born
in the flesh, Nicodemus,

47:01.036 --> 47:04.606
but in order to see heaven
you must be born again

47:04.639 --> 47:05.573
in His spirit.

47:07.076 --> 47:10.578
But I have done everything
by the law of Moses.

47:10.612 --> 47:12.413
I fear God.
I have been a student

47:12.447 --> 47:14.049
of the scriptures
since I was a child.

47:14.083 --> 47:16.484
Your salvation does not come
from anything that you do.

47:17.987 --> 47:19.654
It comes from
what you believe.

47:21.489 --> 47:23.025
Well, then,
help me understand.

47:25.527 --> 47:28.363
God loves the world,
Nicodemus.

47:29.664 --> 47:31.299
He wants his children back.

47:32.467 --> 47:33.635
All of them.

47:36.071 --> 47:38.940
Even those
who do not obey the law?

47:38.973 --> 47:41.342
- God is holy. He condemns sin.
- You're right.

47:42.710 --> 47:45.547
So there must be a sacrifice
that will pay for man's sin

47:45.580 --> 47:47.448
once and for all.

47:47.482 --> 47:51.419
There is no Passover lamb able to
cover man's sin once and for all.

47:52.320 --> 47:54.622
A sacrifice like that
would have to be perfect.

47:56.058 --> 47:57.358
Like God himself.

48:09.704 --> 48:10.939
Like God himself.

48:22.550 --> 48:24.786
Nicodemus!
What are you doing out here?

48:25.453 --> 48:26.989
Fresh air.

48:27.022 --> 48:29.657
It is rather stuffy
in there.

48:29.691 --> 48:32.427
Well, we've already met
with the Roman Commander

48:32.460 --> 48:34.863
and we have a plan
to trap this Nazarene.

48:34.896 --> 48:38.833
It seems this Jesus has been
causing trouble all over Israel.

48:38.867 --> 48:41.502
We are meeting again in a
few minutes at synagogue.

48:42.271 --> 48:45.140
We can expect you
to be there?

48:45.174 --> 48:46.841
Yes, of course.

48:48.743 --> 48:49.677
We must...

48:49.711 --> 48:52.014
We must, we must stop this,
this radical.

48:52.047 --> 48:53.882
Agreed.
And we will.

49:15.137 --> 49:18.606
<i>♪ Now these
walls are pressing in</i>

49:18.640 --> 49:21.910
<i>♪ Crushing me down
'til I cannot breathe</i>

49:21.943 --> 49:25.446
<i>♪ Traditions fail
to bring me peace</i>

49:25.480 --> 49:26.714
<i>♪ How can I stay?</i>

49:27.715 --> 49:31.987
<i>♪ How could I leave?</i>

49:32.021 --> 49:35.490
<i>♪ Is this real what I've seen?</i>

49:35.523 --> 49:39.094
<i>♪ Is this man
the promised King?</i>

49:39.128 --> 49:42.064
<i>♪ Is my world closing in</i>

49:42.797 --> 49:45.533
<i>♪ Around me?</i>

49:45.566 --> 49:49.104
<i>♪ Oh, am I trapped
in these walls?</i>

49:50.139 --> 49:52.573
<i>♪ Am I deaf to his call?</i>

49:53.541 --> 49:56.911
<i>♪ And am I the blind man?</i>

49:56.945 --> 50:00.015
<i>♪ Am I the blind man?</i>

50:00.049 --> 50:04.987
<i>♪ Am I the blind man after</i>

50:05.853 --> 50:10.192
<i>♪ All? ♪</i>

50:34.582 --> 50:37.952
Even the wind
and the waves obey him.

50:37.987 --> 50:41.723
Last night he commanded a storm to
stop, and it did.

50:42.924 --> 50:44.726
Who exactly is he?

50:44.759 --> 50:46.527
Look, I don't know,

50:46.561 --> 50:49.131
but the Pharisees in
Jerusalem call him an outlaw.

50:49.164 --> 50:51.166
Look,

50:51.200 --> 50:53.668
I don't think we can ever
show our faces there again.

50:53.701 --> 50:56.171
Why not?
He's a miracle worker.

50:56.205 --> 50:57.972
- A teacher.
- A healer, a prophet.

50:58.706 --> 50:59.907
A deliverer.

51:00.742 --> 51:02.111
Awake.

51:02.144 --> 51:05.180
Master, how much did you hear us say?

51:06.148 --> 51:08.283
I heard you talking about
the older brother.

51:08.816 --> 51:09.884
What do you mean?

51:10.752 --> 51:12.754
Remember the story I told

51:12.787 --> 51:16.058
about the wealthy farmer's son
who rebelled and ran away

51:16.091 --> 51:17.658
but then returned
to his father?

51:17.692 --> 51:18.926
- Yes.
- Of course.

51:18.960 --> 51:21.196
I never told you how
the older brother responded.

51:21.230 --> 51:22.730
Instead of rejoicing,

51:22.764 --> 51:24.632
he grew in jealousy
toward his little brother

51:24.665 --> 51:26.968
and bitterness
toward his father.

51:27.002 --> 51:30.039
He didn't want to accept that someone
who broke all the rules of sinful living

51:30.072 --> 51:33.008
should be welcomed back home
with such celebration.

51:34.243 --> 51:36.677
The Pharisees?

51:36.711 --> 51:38.646
If you have eyes to see,
John, then let them see.

51:40.182 --> 51:43.085
The Pharisees are acting
like the older brother.

51:43.118 --> 51:45.720
The rebel son
gets the fattened calf.

51:47.156 --> 51:48.689
You...

51:48.723 --> 51:51.592
You're suggesting that
Almighty God welcomes back

51:51.626 --> 51:54.129
any sinner no matter
what they've done?

51:54.163 --> 51:55.297
He does more than that, Judas.

51:56.365 --> 51:57.732
He goes after them.

51:58.800 --> 52:02.104
He's like a good shepherd
who has, say, 100 sheep.

52:03.738 --> 52:05.340
If one of them wandered off
and was lost...

52:07.042 --> 52:09.811
the shepherd would
leave the 99 others

52:09.844 --> 52:13.648
and go into the darkness
to search for that one.

52:14.882 --> 52:16.318
And when
the shepherd found it,

52:16.351 --> 52:19.388
he would rescue it,
embrace it

52:19.421 --> 52:21.789
and joyfully carry it
all the way home.

52:22.957 --> 52:24.126
And when he returns home,

52:24.159 --> 52:26.661
he will call together his
friends and his neighbors,

52:26.694 --> 52:28.863
saying, "Rejoice with me

52:28.896 --> 52:30.865
"because I have found
the one that was lost."

52:32.101 --> 52:34.702
In the same way,
there is more joy in heaven

52:34.735 --> 52:38.240
over one lost sinner who
repents and returns to God...

52:39.807 --> 52:43.011
than over 99 others
who don't need to repent.

52:49.084 --> 52:52.121
Um...
where exactly are we going?

52:53.322 --> 52:55.756
- Gadarenes.
- What?

52:56.458 --> 52:59.361
Gadarenes? No.

52:59.394 --> 53:01.230
No, this is the wrong side

53:01.263 --> 53:03.332
of the Galilee
for the Jews, Peter.

53:03.365 --> 53:05.700
It's full of pigs
and Gentiles.

53:05.733 --> 53:07.869
It's where the Master
wants us to go.

53:09.238 --> 53:10.172
- So we go.
- So we go.

53:10.205 --> 53:12.207
Are those graves?

53:12.241 --> 53:16.011
Gentiles, pigs
and the dead? Well, great!

53:16.044 --> 53:19.448
Let's just break all the laws
of Moses while we're at it!

53:19.481 --> 53:23.718
Hey, everyone! Let's drink a cup
of blood from a strangled goat!

53:24.819 --> 53:26.687
What are we doing here?

53:28.190 --> 53:29.724
Leaving the 99...

53:31.193 --> 53:32.227
to rescue the one.

53:38.233 --> 53:39.734
- To rescue the one?
- Yes.

53:40.801 --> 53:44.006
No. No, he leads us
across the sea,

53:44.039 --> 53:47.342
through a storm
that nearly drowns us

53:47.376 --> 53:50.345
to help some lunatic
in chains?

53:50.379 --> 53:52.114
We're not supposed
to be here.

53:52.147 --> 53:53.881
- You've already forgotten.
- Forgotten what?

53:55.017 --> 53:57.219
When you were the one.

53:57.252 --> 53:59.787
<i>♪ He called me by name</i>

54:00.455 --> 54:02.991
<i>♪ I was under a tree</i>

54:03.025 --> 54:05.294
<i>♪ He came just to find me</i>

54:05.327 --> 54:07.962
<i>♪ And he told me who I am</i>

54:07.996 --> 54:10.232
<i>♪ He called me by name</i>

54:10.265 --> 54:12.800
<i>♪ Like my net I was empty</i>

54:12.833 --> 54:15.404
<i>♪ He calmed
the storm inside me</i>

54:16.305 --> 54:18.006
<i>♪ And life began</i>

54:18.040 --> 54:20.775
<i>♪ He left the 99</i>

54:20.808 --> 54:24.413
<i>♪ When you were the one
When you were the one</i>

54:25.314 --> 54:28.417
<i>♪ Yes, he left the 99</i>

54:28.450 --> 54:30.285
<i>♪ When I was the one</i>

54:30.319 --> 54:32.421
<i>♪ Now that man is the one</i>

54:33.955 --> 54:38.227
<i>♪ He is the one</i>

54:38.260 --> 54:40.362
Fine, we get it,

54:40.395 --> 54:42.431
but at what point
is it not worth the risk?

54:42.464 --> 54:44.499
Not worth the risk?

54:44.533 --> 54:47.402
- That woman at the well...
- What?

54:47.436 --> 54:50.472
<i>♪ That small
man hiding in the tree</i>

54:50.505 --> 54:53.342
<i>♪ The lame man lowered
through the roof</i>

54:53.375 --> 54:57.079
<i>♪ The bleeding woman
in the street</i>

54:57.112 --> 54:59.414
<i>♪ The leper, the blind man
The deaf and the lame</i>

54:59.448 --> 55:01.116
<i>♪ The sick and the broken</i>

55:01.149 --> 55:05.487
<i>♪ He knows their name ♪</i>

55:05.520 --> 55:08.090
Dorian.
Come to me.

55:08.123 --> 55:10.225
My name is Legion.

55:11.360 --> 55:13.996
For there are many of us
within him.

55:14.029 --> 55:17.065
That is a lie.
That is not who you are.

55:17.099 --> 55:20.868
Son of God,
do not bother us!

55:20.901 --> 55:23.572
You are Dorian, a child of
God, and he loves you.

55:23.605 --> 55:26.141
No, no.

55:26.174 --> 55:29.344
We beg you.
If you are going to cast us out,

55:29.378 --> 55:32.180
then send us
into that herd of pigs.

55:32.214 --> 55:34.849
Anywhere but
to the distant place!

55:34.882 --> 55:37.019
Dorian. Be free!

55:52.301 --> 55:54.469
- You! Get out of here!
- Stay back!

55:54.503 --> 55:55.870
He killed our pigs!

55:55.903 --> 55:57.572
He delivered this man
from devils.

55:57.606 --> 55:59.974
And delivered us
into poverty!

56:00.008 --> 56:03.145
You're not welcome here,
miracle worker.

56:03.178 --> 56:04.879
Put your swords away.
We'll leave.

56:11.553 --> 56:13.021
Deliverer.

56:14.289 --> 56:16.091
Healer.

56:16.124 --> 56:18.193
Where are you going?
Please, let me come with you.

56:18.226 --> 56:21.862
No, Dorian. Stay...

56:21.896 --> 56:24.232
and tell your people what
the Lord has done for you.

56:25.200 --> 56:27.602
They won't listen to me.
Not yet.

56:27.636 --> 56:29.338
But they will listen
to you.

56:31.039 --> 56:32.274
Dorian?

56:34.109 --> 56:35.010
Mother...

56:35.677 --> 56:36.578
You're back!

56:38.946 --> 56:41.316
I can see your eyes again.
What happened?

56:41.350 --> 56:44.186
<i>♪ He knew me by name</i>

56:45.087 --> 56:47.556
<i>♪ He called out in the night</i>

56:47.589 --> 56:49.924
<i>♪ Like a piercing light</i>

56:50.559 --> 56:52.361
<i>♪ He saw me</i>

56:52.394 --> 56:56.398
<i>♪ I won't be the same</i>

